  "texts": [
    "Thus, player A is trying to show that y is not accessible to x, while player E is trying to block A's argument.Now consider the following condition on a partial-state frame F:• R⇒win -if xR i y, then ∀y ′ ⊑ y ∃x ′ ⊑ x ∀x ′′ ⊑ x ′ ∃y ′′ ≬ y ′: x ′′ R i y ′′.This condition says that if xR i y, then E has a winning strategy in the accessibility game G(F, x, y, i), in line with our way of thinking about the accessibility game above.",
    "◁ Now we will show that R-rule and R⇒win characterize closure of RO(S, ⊑) under ■ i.Proposition 2.30 (First-order Characterization of Closure of RO(S, ⊑) under ■ i).",
    "For any poset ⟨S, ⊑⟩ and binary relation R i on S, the following are equivalent:1.",
    "RO(S, ⊑) is closed under ■ i; 2.",
    "R i and ⊑ satisfy R-rule and R⇒win."
  ]
